      "content": "i get that but my doctor is always so dismissive and i hate having to book appointments for every little thing. i've been reading online that if you have a healthy diet and stay active you don't need as much blood thinner. like, since i'm not eating a ton of greens or taking extra supplements, wouldn't a lower dose like 2mg actually be a better \"maintenance\" level for someone in my shape? it just feels like overkill right now.",
